        "details": "<p class=\"mw-empty-elt\">\n\n</p>\n<p>The <b>black-tailed crake</b> (<i>Porzana bicolor</i>) is a species of bird in the family Rallidae. It is found in Bangladesh, Bhutan, China, India, Laos, Myanmar, Nepal, Thailand and Vietnam.\n</p>\n<h2><span id=\"Description\">Description</span></h2>\n<p>It is slate-gray with a chestnut brown back. Its eyes are red. Its slender legs are pinkish-red.\n</p>\n\n<p>Its natural habitat is subtropical or tropical moist montane forests.\n</p>\n<h2><span id=\"References\">References</span></h2>\n\n\n<p><br></p> "
