        "details": " <p class=\"mw-empty-elt\">\n</p>\n\n<p>The <b>blue-winged minla</b> (<i>Actinodura cyanouroptera</i>), also known as the <b>blue-winged siva</b>, is a species of bird in the family Leiothrichidae.\n</p><p>It has in the past been placed in the genus <i>Minla</i> and also in the monotypic <i>Siva</i>.</p><p>It is found in the Indian subcontinent and Southeast Asia, ranging across Bangladesh, Bhutan, Cambodia, China, India, Laos, Malaysia, Myanmar, Nepal, Thailand, Tibet, and Vietnam. Its natural habitat is subtropical or tropical moist montane forests.</p>\n<h2><span id=\"References\">References</span></h2>"
