        "details": " <p class=\"mw-empty-elt\">\n</p>\n<p><b>Brandt's mountain finch</b> (<i>Leucosticte brandti</i>), also known as the <b>black-headed mountain-finch</b>, is a species of finch in the family Fringillidae.\nIt is found in Afghanistan, Bhutan, China, India, Kazakhstan, Nepal, Pakistan, Russia, Tajikistan, and Turkmenistan.\nIts natural habitat is temperate grassland.\n</p>\n<h2><span id=\"References\">References</span></h2>\n\n\n\n<p><br></p>"
