        "details": " <p class=\"mw-empty-elt\">\n</p>\n\n<p>The <b>broad-billed warbler</b> (<i>Tickellia hodgsoni</i>) is a species of bush warbler (family Cettiidae). It was formerly included in the \"Old World warbler\" assemblage, and belongs to the monotypic genus <i><b>Tickellia</b></i>.\n</p><p>It is found in Bhutan, China, India, Laos, Myanmar, Nepal, and Vietnam. Its natural habitats are subtropical or tropical moist lowland forest and subtropical or tropical moist montane forest.\n</p>\n<h2><span id=\"References\">References</span></h2>\n\n\n<p><br></p>\n\n<p><br></p>"
