        "details": " <p class=\"mw-empty-elt\">\n</p>\n<p>The <b>brown accentor</b> (<i>Prunella fulvescens</i>) is a species of bird in the family Prunellidae. It is found in Afghanistan, China, India, Kazakhstan, Mongolia, Nepal, Pakistan, Russia, Tajikistan, Turkmenistan, and Uzbekistan.\n</p><p>Its natural habitat is Mediterranean-type shrubby vegetation.\n</p>\n<h2><span id=\"References\">References</span></h2>\n\n\n<p><br></p>"
