    "brown crake": {
        "id": "b113",
        "name": "Brown Crake",
        "order": "Gruifirmes",
        "family": familyname.Rallidae,
        "genus": "Zapornia", "species": "akool",
        "nepali": " ",
        "details": " <p class=\"mw-empty-elt\">\n</p>\n<p>The <b>brown crake</b> (<i>Amaurornis akool</i>), or <b>brown bush-hen</b>, is a waterbird in the rail and crake family (<i>Rallidae</i>) found in South Asia.\n</p><p>Its genus name, <i>Amaurornis</i>, comes from the Greek <i>amauros</i>, meaning \"dusky\" or \"brown\" and <i>ornis</i>, meaning \"bird\". The species name, <i>akool</i>, is of uncertain origin.  It may come from Hindu mythology, or it may be a derivation of the Sinhalese word <i>kukkula</i>, which is used for both moorhen and watercock.</p><p>The brown crake makes alarming call when it see predator or human to alert other birds.\n</p>\n<h2><span id=\"References\">References</span></h2>\n<h3><span id=\"Notes\">Notes</span></h3>\n\n<h3><span id=\"Cited_texts\">Cited texts</span></h3>\n<p><cite id=\"CITEREFJobling2010\" class=\"citation book\">Jobling, James A. (2010). <i>The Helm Dictionary of Scientific Bird Names</i>. London, UK: Christopher Helm. ISBN\u00a0<bdi>978-1-4081-2501-4</bdi>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Helm+Dictionary+of+Scientific+Bird+Names&amp;rft.place=London%2C+UK&amp;rft.pub=Christopher+Helm&amp;rft.date=2010&amp;rft.isbn=978-1-4081-2501-4&amp;rft.aulast=Jobling&amp;rft.aufirst=James+A.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Farchive.org%2Fdetails%2FHelm_Dictionary_of_Scientific_Bird_Names_by_James_A._Jobling&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABrown+crake\"></span><link rel=\"mw-deduplicated-inline-style\" href=\"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r951705291\"></p>\n\n<p><br></p>"
    },
