        "details": " <p class=\"mw-empty-elt\">\n</p>\n<p>The <b>brown bush warbler</b> (<i>Locustella luteoventris</i>) is a songbird species. Formerly placed in the \"Old World warbler\" assemblage, it is now placed in the newly recognized family Locustellidae.\n</p><p>It is found in Bangladesh, Bhutan, China, Hong Kong, India, Myanmar, Nepal, Thailand, and Vietnam. Its natural habitat is boreal forests during breeding and subtropical and tropical forest in the winter quarters.\n</p>\n<h2><span id=\"References\">References</span></h2>"
