        "details": " <p class=\"mw-empty-elt\">\n</p>\n<p>The <b>chestnut-bellied rock thrush</b> (<i>Monticola rufiventris</i>) is a species of bird in the family Muscicapidae.\n</p><p>It is found in the northern regions of the Indian subcontinent, eastwards towards parts of Southeast Asia.  Its range includes Bangladesh, Bhutan, India, Tibet, Laos, Myanmar, Nepal, Pakistan, Thailand, and Vietnam.\n</p><p>Its natural habitat is temperate forests. \n</p>\n<h2><span id=\"Gallery\">Gallery</span></h2>\n<ul class=\"gallery mw-gallery-traditional\"><li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 255px\">\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 255px\">\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 255px\">\n</ul><h2><span id=\"References\">References</span></h2>"
