        "details": " <p class=\"mw-empty-elt\">\n</p>\n<p>The <b>chestnut-crowned laughingthrush</b> (<i>Trochalopteron erythrocephalum</i>) is a species of bird in the family Leiothrichidae. It is found in Bhutan, China, India, and Nepal.\n</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The silver-eared laughingthrush, formerly included as a subspecies, is now usually regarded as a separate species.\n</p>\n<h2><span id=\"References\">References</span></h2>\n\n<ul><li>BirdLife International 2004.  Garrulax erythrocephalus.   2006 IUCN Red List of Threatened Species.   Downloaded on 25 July 2007.</li></ul><h2><span id=\"External_links\">External links</span></h2>\n<ul><li>Images at ADW</li></ul>"
